# Read by oxfmt (in addition to .gitignore) per `oxfmt --help`. Keeps
# oxfmt out of vendored upstream code that should track upstream byte-
# for-byte — every byte oxfmt touches under vendor/ is a future re-
# vendor diff that has to be undone.
#
# .config/oxfmtrc.json's `ignorePatterns` block is supposed to handle
# this but doesn't (verified locally on oxfmt's latest; `**/vendor/**`
# in ignorePatterns has no effect under `oxfmt -c <config> --write .`).
# Pulling vendor/ out via .prettierignore is the working escape hatch.

# Vendored upstream trees.
vendor/

# Build artifacts.
dist/
coverage/
coverage-isolated/

# Generated reports / schemas.
docs/api-index.md
